node.title: Sir Lewis Hamilton receives his knighthood days after dramatic F1 finale
node.description: Just days after coming agonisingly short of winning his eighth championship in the highly controversial Abu Dhabi Grand Prix, Sir Lewis receives his knighthood from Prince Charles.

node.title: Racist remarks in video at judge's home prompt calls for her to quit
node.description: The video showed an apparent foiled burglary at the Louisiana home of Lafayette City Court Judge Michelle Odinet.

node.title: Blinken cuts Asia trip short after journalist tests positive for COVID
node.description: The secretary will be returning to Washington, D.C., "out of an abundance of caution," State Department spokesman Ned Price said.

node.title: Retail sales rose slightly in November as holiday shopping began.
node.description: The increase in spending continued for a fourth straight month despite an increase in coronavirus cases and higher prices on goods because of inflation.

node.title: Why December Child Tax Credit Payment Might Be the Last
node.description: December 15 sees the sixth and final payment of the expanded child tax credit amid a fight to get it extended.

node.title: Will our bottom line survive the Omicron variant? The government is hoping so
node.description: The federal government will use today's mid-year budget update to spruik upgraded forecasts for job creation over the next four years, as the Opposition says there is little room for complacency after previous turnarounds ended in more lockdowns and a recession.

node.title: Kristi Noem continues push to ban trans girls from female sports
node.description: The proposal comes on the heels of what is believed to be the deadliest year for transgender people in the U.S.

node.title: Ending Child Tax Credit could push 10 million kids into poverty
node.description: As stimulus programs wind down, experts warn that slashing the Child Tax Credit could put many families "on the brink."

node.title: ‘Rumble’ Review: He’s Not Ready, but His Coach Is Very Persuasive
node.description: Steve is being pressed into service as a wrestler in training, but if he had a choice he’d prefer a rumba to a rumble.

node.title: Blinken Cuts Short Asia Trip After Journalist on His Plane Tests Positive for Covid
node.description: Citing the need for caution, the secretary of state expressed “deep regret” to Thailand’s deputy prime minister before returning to the U. S. earlier than planned.

node.title: Five Republican governors seek vaccine exemptions, escalating a fight with the Pentagon.
node.description: The move comes as the Pentagon released a new order this week saying that National Guard members who do not get vaccinated would receive a general order of reprimand, essentially ending their careers.

node.title: Joe Biden to Sign Bill Punishing China for Uyghur Forced Labor in Xinjiang
node.description: A compromise version of the legislation was passed in the House of Representatives on Tuesday after months of negotiations.

node.title: House and Senate vote to raise debt ceiling by $2.5 trillion
node.description: Lifting the debt limit by $2.5 trillion would mean the issue would not come up again until 2023.

node.title: More than 800,000 Americans have died of COVID. Vaccines could have saved 163,000.
node.description: The Kaiser Family Foundation estimated COVID-19's avoidable toll since June, when vaccines became widely available.

node.title: European natural gas prices are soaring again.
node.description: With cold weather approaching, worries over gas inventories and tensions over Ukraine are stoking the highest prices in more than a decade.

node.title: Man Exonerated in Malcolm X Murder Files Lawsuit Against New York State
node.description: Muhammad A. Aziz filed the claim on Tuesday, along with a notice seeking a settlement with the city, for the toll that being “unjustly branded as a convicted murderer” for 55 years took on his life.

node.title: Hong Kong researchers find that two doses of China’s Sinovac vaccine are inadequate against Omicron.
node.description: The research suggests that the Chinese vaccine had little effect against Omicron and that the efficacy of the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine seemed to wane.

node.title: Why Hasan Piker Has Been Banned From Twitch
node.description: Popular streamer Hasan Piker, better known as HasanAbi, has been banned from Twitch and his channel is no longer accessible. Here is everything you need to know.

node.title: Can I Still See the Geminid Meteor Shower, and When Does It End?
node.description: Skywatchers still have a few days to catch the Geminids before they return in December 2022.

node.title: Donald Trump Must Be Blamed For Capitol Attack, Says Jan 6 Rally Organizer

node.title: Bumble Profile of Wife Telling Husband to 'Pack His Bags' Goes Viral
node.description: The wife even made a photo of their wedding day as the main image on her account on the dating app.

node.title: House votes to hold Mark Meadows in contempt of Congress

node.title: What's behind the push for a fourth stimulus check

node.title: In ‘With Love,’ Gloria Calderón Kellett Comes Home for the Holidays

node.title: Woman, 22, Dies From COVID Soon After Giving Birth: 'She Gave Her Life for Her'

node.title: Search underway for 25 missing Indonesians after boat capsizes off Malaysia coast, killing 11

node.title: Family to get $5 million settlement over Black motorist's death
node.description: Body camera footage showed Javier Ambler telling the deputies he was not resisting and that he could not breathe.

node.title: Muslim advocacy group exec fired for alleged aid to Muslim hate group
node.description: CAIR-Ohio says Romin Iqbal recorded its meetings and passed information to the other group for several years in what it called "an incredible violation of trust."

node.title: New Jersey Shakes Up Men’s College Basketball Rankings
node.description: No. 16 Seton Hall has two wins over top-10 teams, and Rutgers upset No. 1 Purdue after a rough start. They revived their rivalry Sunday after a one-year hiatus.
